    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into strips</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion wedges</strong>,<strong> pepper strips </strong>and<strong> sweet potato wedges </strong>to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>ground cumin</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> Mexican-style marinade</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> to the <strong>Mexican-style</strong> <strong>marinade </strong>and give everything a good mix up, then set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have had 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>marinated fish </strong>to the tray[s]</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 12-15 min or until the fish is cooked through and the vegetables are tender \u2013 this is your <strong>Mexican-style fish tray bake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>lime[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mexican-style-cod-tray-bake-with-lime-and-yoghurt/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Mexican-style fish tray bake</strong> drizzled with your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong> and a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
